Based on the documentation, when using [multi-user setup ](https://flask-dance.readthedocs.io/en/latest/multi-user.html) we're supposed to return False to disable Flask default behavior for saving the token. With the new update regarding #253 ,  now if we want to redirect, we need to do this after the `@oauth_authorized` signal.
```python
@oauth_authorized.connect
def logged_in(blueprint, token):
    blueprint.token = token
    next_url = flask.session["next_url"]
    return flask.redirect(next_url)
```

How can we return a flask.redirect and return False at the same time in the same method? 
It does not seem possible to me. Is there a new behaviour I need to know in order to disable the default token saving?

